$ Excel: Sheet tabs

The sheet tabs are located at the bottom of a window/worksheet. They're also referred to as *workbook tabs*.

sa:

  The `→ Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Window` property `displayWorkbookTabs` and method `scrollWorkbookTabs()`

  → Microsoft/Office/Excel/GUI/Ribbon/tabs/File/Options/Advanced[File -> Options -> Advanced] -> Display options for this → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Workbook -> Show sheet tabs

  → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/CommandBars/Ply[`commandBars("Ply")`]
